  "type": "EPCISDocument",
  "schemaVersion": "2.0",
  "creationDate": "2024-03-15T14:30:00.000Z",
  "_comment_architecture": [
    "Battery commissioning event with product, location, and organization master data inline.",
    "masterDataAvailableFor carries:",
    "  - gs1: product master data (productName, gtin, netWeight, countryOfOrigin, regulatoryInformation)",
    "  - battery:-prefixed PRODUCT-LEVEL attributes (batteryCategory, batteryChemistry, ratedCapacity,",
    "    ratedEnergy, batteryModelIdentifier, facilityIdentifier, manufacturerIdentifier); these",
    "    describe the GTIN and are identical across every lot of this SKU. GS1 has no native term",
    "    for them yet; keeping them in the product entry means any downstream consumer gets the",
    "    full product card in one place.",
    "  - cross-cutting passport metadata (schema:schemaVersion, schema:status, dpp:reportingGranularity,",
    "    dpp:lastUpdated) per BatteryPass-Ready v1.3 longlist attributes #1-#4.",
    "  - gs1:hasSerialNumber surfaced explicitly even though it is also encoded in the EPC URN",
    "    as the (21) AI; the SAMM v1.3 export expects an explicit field. The full gs1:",
    "    prefix is required here because hasSerialNumber has no shortcut in the EPCIS",
    "    base context (only serialNumber does).",
    "ilmd is INTENTIONALLY ABSENT: we have no lot-specific data to assert on this event.",
    "Observation-specific readings (stateOfHealth, stateOfCharge, cycleCount at this moment) ride",
    "in sensorElementList, the EPCIS-native place for sensor observations.",
    "",
    "HTTP header: GS1-Extensions: dpp=https://ref.openepcis.io/extensions/common/core/,battery=https://ref.openepcis.io/extensions/eu/battery/",
    "The header is REQUIRED for an OpenEPCIS repository to engage v1.3 validation (JSON Schema",
    "+ SHACL shapes per namespace) and to expose the SAMM v1.3 export endpoint that GEFEG",
    "batterypass-ready conformance tests will hit.",
    "See: extensions/common/core/docs/EPCIS_MASTERDATA_AND_EXTENSIONS.md",
    "GS1 demo prefix 952 (7-digit GCP: 9521234)."
  ],
